14/10/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Local officials signed a memorandum of intent Wednesday (October 13th) with officials from Russian gas giant Gazprom regarding the possibility of the South Stream pipeline transiting Romania, Alexey Miller, chairman of Gazprom's management committee, announced. 
The South Stream project envisions construction of a pipeline to deliver Russian natural gas to Europe. 
Romania is also a partner in the Nabucco project, which would transport natural gas to Europe from the Middle East. 
Miller came to Bucharest to discuss several projects in the energy sector. 
In addition to determining Romania's role in the South Stream project, Gazprom also intends to develop projects with the largest local gas producer, Romgaz, concerning natural gas storage facilities and thermo energy. 
(Reuters, Hotnews.ro - 13/10/10)
